main event: A red object with a fiery trail was observed in Burlington, Iowa.
interesting points: Multiple reports were received, approximately 94 people called in about the fiery object., The object was observed moving horizontally across the sky north of Burlington., The sighting lasted for about 10 seconds before disappearing from sight., The object was concluded to possibly be a balloon but was marked as insufficient data for evaluation., The radio station in Burlington received numerous calls regarding the sighting.
sighted object: red object with a fiery trail
